             Samoa Observatory -- Cape Matatula, American Samoa
     __________________________________________________________________

      Samoa Observatory is located on the eastern end of the island of
   Tutuila, American Samoa on a ridge overlooking the South Pacific Ocean.
      Established in 1973, the Samoa Observatory has survived two major
      hurricanes with only minor damage. A staff of 2 operates the year
    around facility commuting to work from staff housing near Pago Pago.
    Samoa Observatory had the distinction of obtaining 30% of its daytime
                          power from solar panels.


